@@TJvDirectorySpy.Active
Description:
Modify this property to pause/resume the thread.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDirectorySpy.Directory
Description:
This property is the directory you want to spy. By default, this property is set to 'c:', Jvt you can spy everything you want. (ex c:file.ext, d:dir1, ...).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDirectorySpy.Mask
Description:
Modify this property to set the mask for the modifications you want to spy. You can spy FileName changes, directory name changes, attriJvte changes, size changes, last write changes and secutiry changes. Be sure to be under windows NT to use the dmSecurityChange flag, or it will cause an Exception.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDirectorySpy.OnChange
Description:
This event is called when a modification has been detected.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDirectorySpy.Recursive
Description:
This property specifies if you want to spy the directory only or subdirectories too. if this property is true and Directory is c:, you will be warned for every modification on file/directory on the c: drive.

